                "---\n",
                "title: \"Performance tricks\"\n",
                "code-fold: show\n",
                "---\n",
                "\n",
                "## Hurwitz Check\n",
                "\n",
                "Create our nice model.\n",
                "Assume to have run the `poles` function and that you have a vector of eigenvalues. For simplicity I will create an arbitrary vector with the first 100 values in $-1$ and the last 100 values as random around $0$."
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "2",
            "cell_type": "code",
            "metadata": {
            },
            "source": [
                "using BenchmarkTools\n",
                "\n",
                "vbig = [zeros(ComplexF64,100).-1 ; rand(ComplexF64,100).-0.5];\n",
                "\n",
                "vbig[[1,end]]"
            ],
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "output_type": "execute_result",
                    "execution_count": 1,
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": "2-element Vector{ComplexF64}:\n               -1.0 + 0.0im\n 0.3445689899748905 + 0.7961802504867754im"
                    },
                    "metadata": {
                    }
                }
            ],
            "execution_count": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "3",
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {
            },
            "source": [
                "\n",
                "### `for` loop\n",
                "\n",
                "\n",
                "With a naive approach we check if all the  elements are in the LHP: make a function that iterates and returns false if it hits a pole with positive real part.\n",
                ""
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "4",
            "cell_type": "code",
            "metadata": {
            },
            "source": [
                "function isHurwitz(v)\n",
                "    for i in eachindex(v)\n",
                "        if real(v[i])>0.0\n",
                "            return false\n",
                "        end\n",
                "    end\n",
                "    return true\n",
                "end\n",
                "\n",
                "@benchmark isHurwitz($(Ref(vbig))[])"
            ],
